{% comment %}
  snippets/header-account.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ROW 3c: Account link — icon + label, switches between guest and logged-in.

  VARIABLES PASSED IN: none.

  GLOBALS READ DIRECTLY:
    customer          — nil when guest, object when logged in.
                        Shopify sets this automatically on every request.
    routes.account_url — resolves to /account (Shopify redirects guests
                         to /account/login automatically, so one URL works
                         for both states).

  CALLER (sections/header.liquid):
    {% render 'header-account' %}

  STATES:
    Guest      → label "Sign in / Register", aria-label "Sign in or register"
    Logged in  → label "Hi, [first name]",   aria-label "My account"

  STEP 3 NOTE:
    When you add a customer account drawer or a login modal, wire the click
    event to the [data-account-trigger] attribute on the <a> tag rather than
    changing the href — keeps this snippet markup-stable.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}


  href="{{ routes.account_url }}"
  class="header__account"
  aria-label="{% if customer %}My account{% else %}Sign in or register{% endif %}"
  data-account-trigger
>
  {% render 'icon', name: 'account', size: 20, class: 'header__account-icon' %}
  <span class="header__account-label">
    {%- if customer -%}
      Hi, {{ customer.first_name }}
    {%- else -%}
      Sign in / Register
    {%- endif -%}
  </span>
</a>